00:33:18,056 --> 00:33:20,966
on AVPlayerViewController,
new AV kit APIs


752
00:33:20,966 --> 00:33:22,406
that are introduced
here at WWDC.


753
00:33:23,456 --> 00:33:27,206
This is available on both
iPhone and iPad and has been


754
00:33:27,206 --> 00:33:28,916
since the initial introduction.


755
00:33:29,136 --> 00:33:32,826
I want to sort of circle back
to the very first bullet here,


756
00:33:32,826 --> 00:33:34,306
the short video plays
before content.


757
00:33:34,756 --> 00:33:35,706
This is really important.


758
00:33:36,016 --> 00:33:38,256
This is not an
interstitial-style ad.


759
00:33:38,546 --> 00:33:41,036
This is something to be
played before your content,


760
00:33:41,076 --> 00:33:41,976
so you need to make sure


761
00:33:41,976 --> 00:33:44,606
that you actually have a
video to play after it.


762
00:33:44,866 --> 00:33:47,916
We don't want - it's not
supported for you to attempt


763
00:33:47,916 --> 00:33:50,946
to use this just to play a
random ad at a random time.


764
00:33:51,246 --> 00:33:52,986
Make sure that you have
content to follow it;


765
00:33:52,986 --> 00:33:55,286
that's what the API
is designed for.


766
00:33:57,496 --> 00:34:00,626
So setting up and playback,
also fairly straightforward.


767
00:34:00,626 --> 00:34:01,476
You're going to start off


