00:34:38,746 --> 00:34:39,755
for it once it's there as well.


787
00:34:40,226 --> 00:34:43,315
And then you're going to
call playPrerollAdWith


788
00:34:43,315 --> 00:34:44,306
CompletionHandler.


789
00:34:44,306 --> 00:34:45,576
You're going to call
this instead


790
00:34:45,576 --> 00:34:47,056
of immediately calling Play.


791
00:34:47,056 --> 00:34:50,696
This tells iAd, "Hey, try
to put a pre-roll video


792
00:34:50,696 --> 00:34:51,735
in there if you've got one.


793
00:34:52,266 --> 00:34:53,376
Play that first."


794
00:34:54,416 --> 00:34:55,636
This takes a completion handler.


795
00:34:55,636 --> 00:34:57,036
It's going to return
an error possibly


796
00:34:57,036 --> 00:34:57,926
if something went wrong.


797
00:34:58,616 --> 00:35:01,986
Inside the completion handler is
your cue to start your content.


798
00:35:02,356 --> 00:35:05,026
You want to make sure you don't
automatically play your content.


799
00:35:05,026 --> 00:35:06,216
You want to pause your content


800
00:35:06,216 --> 00:35:08,256
until this actually
begins playing,


801
00:35:08,906 --> 00:35:11,126
or until the pre-roll
finishes playing and you want


802
00:35:11,126 --> 00:35:14,306
to begin your own content then.


803
00:35:14,306 --> 00:35:15,886
For AVKit it's almost identical.


804
00:35:15,926 --> 00:35:18,236
You're going to create an
AVPlayerViewController instead.


805
00:35:18,236 --> 00:35:19,846
You're going to import
the AVKit headers.


