CompletionHandler.


808
00:35:23,696 --> 00:35:25,056
It has identical semantics


809
00:35:25,056 --> 00:35:26,986
to the MPMediaPlayerController
ones.


810
00:35:27,456 --> 00:35:30,266
Inside the completion handler,
you're going to call player play


811
00:35:30,266 --> 00:35:33,056
to start your own video
content afterward.


812
00:35:33,546 --> 00:35:34,766
This is new in iOS 8.


813
00:35:37,416 --> 00:35:40,536
Just like interstitials, because
this is something that is going


814
00:35:40,536 --> 00:35:43,626
to happen at some point and
you want to have iAd prepare it


815
00:35:43,626 --> 00:35:46,056
for it you need to tell
the iAd framework, "Hey,


816
00:35:46,056 --> 00:35:48,586
I'm going to want to play
pre-rolls in the future."


817
00:35:49,166 --> 00:35:50,896
That allows us to have
the opportunity to go


818
00:35:50,896 --> 00:35:54,656
out to the ad server, grab ads,
and be ready for your request


819
00:35:54,656 --> 00:35:56,586
to play pre-rolls so that
we can actually play one


820
00:35:56,586 --> 00:35:58,886
when the user does
something that requires it.


821
00:35:59,506 --> 00:36:01,766
To do that, just like
interstitials you don't want


822
00:36:01,766 --> 00:36:04,006
to miss these early impressions,
so you're going to want


823
00:36:04,006 --> 00:36:05,346
to start ad requests early


824
00:36:05,726 --> 00:36:07,746
by calling
MPMoviePlayerController


825
00:36:07,876 --> 00:36:09,146
preparePrerollAds.


826
00:36:09,406 --> 00:36:11,626
Again, probably an
application did finish launching


827
00:36:11,626 --> 00:36:15,896
with options or some other early
in your app's life cycle period,


